com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.resthttp

Class GetMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.Message
      • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.OutMessage
        • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.resthttp.GetMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MultiPartGetMessage

    public class GetMessage
extends OutMessage
implements Serializable
    Represents an OutMessage with the method type as GET that will be sent to the server. This message instance is used to 'get' the data from the server.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Neebal Technologies

    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      GetMessage()
      Initializes GetMessage instance
      This will initialize the instance with null resourcePath and no response type and callbacks

      Note: This could be useful for cases where a particular message depends upon another message for its resource path.
      This GetMessage instance will be synchronous in nature

      Since the creation of this object does not require the response type to which the response will be unmarshalled to, simplyreliable api will not do the parsing and will return the raw inputstream of the response in the future callbacks

      • GetMessage

        public GetMessage()

        This will initialize the instance with null resourcePath and no response type and callbacks

        Note: This could be useful for cases where a particular message depends upon another message for its resource path.
        This GetMessage instance will be synchronous in nature

        Since the creation of this object does not require the response type to which the response will be unmarshalled to, simplyreliable api will not do the parsing and will return the raw inputstream of the response in the future callbacks

    • Method Detail

      • getResponseType

        public Type getResponseType()
        Returns:
        a response Type instance representing the entire response structure that is expected out of this get request. Will return a null value if the user has choosen not to let the api do the unmarshalling of the response to the appropriate java objects graph. For this case, in all future callbacks, the api will pass the raw inputstream of the response in all the callbacks.

      • getQueryParams

        public QueryParams getQueryParams()
        Returns:
        the name/value query parameters that need to be appended to this GET request to be sent to the server

      • executeServerCall

        public void executeServerCall(HttpURLConnection connection)
                       throws IOException,
                              GetMessageResponseFileStorageException,
                              CreateMultipartGetMsgFileException
        Description copied from class: OutMessage
        The logic to make a request to the server and getting the response/headers back from the server should be done in this method. The implementation would depend upon the method type using which the request has to be made to the server.
        Note: Different subclass implementations can throw the below exceptions
        Specified by:
        executeServerCall in class OutMessage
        Parameters:
        connection - the HttpURLConnection connection object using which the call needs to be made to the server
        Throws:
        IOException - there was an i/o error at the time of connecting with the server or some error at the time of reading the input data
        GetMessageResponseFileStorageException - if error at the time of saving the response from a GetMessage in the local file system
        CreateMultipartGetMsgFileException - if there is an error in creating the file for the artifact that was downloaded in the MultiPartGetMessage instance

      • getRequestMethod

        public String getRequestMethod()
        Specified by:
        getRequestMethod in class OutMessage
        Returns:
        the string representation of the request method supported by the instance that implements this method. It can be one of the values
        • GET
        • POST
        • PUT
        • DELETE

      • handleResponse

        public boolean handleResponse()
                       throws GetMessageResponseFileStorageException,
                              BadResponseException,
                              InvalidResponseCodeException
        Description copied from class: OutMessage
        Handle the response returned for a particular OutMessage instance.
        Specified by:
        handleResponse in class OutMessage
        Returns:
        a boolean value indicating whether the response was handled completely or no
        Throws:
        GetMessageResponseFileStorageException - if error at the time of saving the response from a GetMessage in the local file system
        BadResponseException - if invalid status code of response was returned from the server
        InvalidResponseCodeException - if the response code returned by the server for this message is invalid

      • isValidCallback

        public boolean isValidCallback(BaseCallback callback)
        Specified by:
        isValidCallback in class Message
        Parameters:
        callback - an instance of BaseCallback
        Returns:
        a boolean value. true if the instance passed is either GetMessageCallback or StreamingResponseCallback. Also when the instance passed is GetMessageCallback, the responseType property of this GetMessage instance cannot be null
